Foreign buyers will have to pay higher taxes on real estate purchased in the UK, and the surplus revenue will be used to support homeless people, Theresa May is preparing to announce at a press conference today.
The move is likely aimed at offsetting Jeremy Corbyn’s success among young voters by promising more affordable housing and high-income measures.
